.TH XIL\-CUES "1" "2026\-04\-24" "xil\-pipeline 0.1.8" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xil\-cues
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xil\-cues
[-h] (--episode EPISODE | --tag TAG) [--show SHOW] [--cues CUES] [--dry-run] [--generate] [--enrich-sfx-config]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Parse a sound cues & music prompts markdown file into an asset manifest, audit the SFX library, and optionally generate new assets or enrich the episode sfx config.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-episode\fR \fI\,EPISODE\/\fR
Episode tag (e.g. S02E03) — derives sfx config path

.TP
\fB\-\-tag\fR \fI\,TAG\/\fR
Raw tag for non\-episodic content (e.g. V01C03, D01)

.TP
\fB\-\-show\fR \fI\,SHOW\/\fR
Show name override (default: from project.json)

.TP
\fB\-\-cues\fR \fI\,CUES\/\fR
Path to cues markdown file (auto\-detected from cues/ if omitted)

.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show audit report and enrichment diff without API calls or sfx config writes
(manifest is always written)

.TP
\fB\-\-generate\fR
Generate NEW assets via ElevenLabs API into SFX/

.TP
\fB\-\-enrich\-sfx\-config\fR
Update episode SFX config with cues\-sheet prompts/durations

